In a bid to promote transparency and equity, the Abuja Municipal Area Council, (AMAC) has opened its first quarter of the 2020 tender bids, with about 180 contractors bidding for projects in the council. Declaring the tender documents bid open, the council chairman, Hon Abdullahi Adamu Candido, said that the bidders are regarded as stakeholders whose immense contributions are needed for the progress of the council. Candido revealed that the council had placed an advertisement calling on bidders from all walks of life to partake in the procurement process, adding that the council is relying on the bidders’ full cooperation while they go through the selection process. Represented by the council secretary, Mrs. Ramat Abisola, the AMAC chairman maintained that as part of the 2017 public procurement Act, that the tender document was provided and opened to allow the council commence the process of service provision as established in the 2020 budgetary appropriation. Speaking to newsmen, the head, department of Works and Housing, Arc Andrew Gaza said that the council is expecting quality output from the bidders. One of the bidders, who spoke to newsmen said that they are impressed with the display of transparency by the council, just as he assured their full support and cooperation.  